TITLE: Workaround for minSpareRows behavior in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Provides a workaround to maintain the previous behavior of minSpareRows when used with TrimRows in Handsontable 8.0.0. It uses the beforeCreateRow hook to block row creation under certain conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/handsontable/handsontable/blob/develop/docs/content/guides/upgrade-and-migration/migrating-from-7.4-to-8.0/migrating-from-7.4-to-8.0.md#2025-04-10_snippet_33

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const hotInstance = new Handsontable(container, {
  data: [
    ['A1', 'B1', 'C1', 'D1', 'E1'],
    ['A2', 'B2', 'C2', 'D2', 'E2'],
    ['A3', 'B3', 'C3', 'D3', 'E3'],
    ['A4', 'B4', 'C4', 'D4', 'E4'],
    ['A5', 'B5', 'C5', 'D5', 'E5'],
  ],
  trimRows: [0],
  beforeCreateRow(index, amount, source) {
    const rowIndexMapper = this.rowIndexMapper;
    // if any row was skipped then block a creation of row execution.
    if (source === 'auto' && rowIndexMapper.getNotSkippedIndexesLength() < rowIndexMapper.getNumberOfIndexes()) {
      return false;
    }
  },
  minSpareRows: 2
});
```

