TITLE: Workaround for Cell Selection Behavior in Handsontable 8.0.0
DESCRIPTION: Provides a workaround to maintain the previous cell selection behavior when clicking on the top-left corner. In 8.0.0, this action selects all cells by default, but this code allows selection of only the first cell.
SOURCE: https://github.com/handsontable/handsontable/blob/develop/docs/content/guides/upgrade-and-migration/migrating-from-7.4-to-8.0/migrating-from-7.4-to-8.0.md#2025-04-10_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
beforeOnCellMouseDown(event, coords) {
  if (coords.col === -1 && coords.row === -1) {
    event.stopImmediatePropagation();
    const visualRow = this.rowIndexMapper.getVisualFromRenderableIndex(0);
    const visualColumn = this.columnIndexMapper.getVisualFromRenderableIndex(0);

    this.selectCell(visualRow, visualColumn);
  }
}
```

