TITLE: New Autofill Hooks Implementation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows the updated implementation of beforeAutofill and afterAutofill hooks in version 9.0 with new parameter structure in JavaScript.
SOURCE: https://github.com/handsontable/handsontable/blob/develop/docs/content/guides/upgrade-and-migration/migrating-from-8.4-to-9.0/migrating-from-8.4-to-9.0.md#2025-04-10_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
new Handsontable(container, {
  data,
  beforeAutofill(selectionData, sourceRange, targetRange, direction) {
    const start = targetRange.from // used to be `start`
    const end = targetRange.to // used to be `end`
    const data = selectionData // used to be `data`
  },
  afterAutofill(fillData, sourceRange, targetRange, direction) {
    const start = targetRange.from // used to be `start`
    const end = targetRange.to // used to be `end`
    const data = fillData // used to be `data`
  }
})
```

